CSS3 background :

CSS3 is going to introduce the 
ability to specify a gradient for 
the background of a box. The 
gradient is created using the 
background-image property 
and, at the time of writing, 
different browsers required a 
different syntax

contarst in the back ground can vary - high, low and screen, to each a benfit depends what do u want as more visibile.

You can specify the dimensions of images using CSS. 
This is very helpful when you use the same sized 
images on several pages of your site.
X Images can be aligned both horizontally and vertically 
using CSS.
X You can use a background image behind the box 
created by any element on a page. 
X Background images can appear just once or be 
repeated across the background of the box.
X You can create image rollover effects by moving the 
background position of an image.
X To reduce the number of images your browser has to 
load, you can create image sprites
